title: JAR
description: Users are dropping off after sign up
creator: raghav7533
insights:
Jar is a financial app designed to simplify savings by encouraging users to save spare change from daily transactions and invest it in digital gold. The app rounds off users' digital payments and automatically invests the small amounts into 24K, 99.9% pure digital gold, stored securely in custodian-managed vaults. With Jar, users can start saving with as little as ₹10 and have the option to either cash out their savings or convert them into physical gold at any time.

I want to know the user's experience

Probe if needed: Can you explain what you liked or disliked about the app?
Probe gently if they give a broad answer: Can you give me an example of a specific feature or aspect of the app that stood out to you?
If the user gives a generic answer, probe with: Can you elaborate on that?
